emotions.name: Joy
texts: I canâ€™t stop smiling and laughing.
Warm excitement spreads through my body.
Everything around me feels bright and welcoming.
I feel energized and eager to move.
My heart feels light and open.
Small things bring me unexpected delight.
I want to share this feeling with others.
Positive thoughts come naturally right now.
I feel emotionally lifted and free.
The moment feels genuinely enjoyable.

emotions.name: Sadness
texts: My chest feels heavy and slow.
I feel withdrawn from everything around me.
Energy drains from my body.
My thoughts feel dark and repetitive.
I want to be alone and quiet.
Emptiness lingers inside me.
I feel emotionally weighed down.
Tears feel close beneath the surface.
Nothing feels motivating or bright.
I feel a deep sense of loss.

emotions.name: Anger
texts: Heat rises quickly inside my body.
My jaw tightens and muscles tense.
I feel an urge to confront someone.
Thoughts feel sharp and aggressive.
I feel wronged and provoked.
I want to push back forcefully.
My patience disappears instantly.
I feel intense irritation building up.
Everything feels unfair right now.
Iâ€™m ready to react without hesitation.

emotions.name: Fear
texts: My heart is pounding rapidly.
I feel a strong urge to escape.
My body feels tense and alert.
Thoughts jump to worst-case scenarios.
I feel threatened and unsafe.
My breathing becomes shallow.
I scan my surroundings for danger.
I feel frozen and uncertain.
Anxiety grips my chest tightly.
I want to protect myself immediately.

emotions.name: Elation
texts: My excitement feels overwhelming and intense.
I feel a rush of exhilaration coursing through me.
Iâ€™m bursting with uncontrollable happiness.
My body feels charged with pure excitement.
I feel on top of the world right now.
Joy feels amplified beyond normal limits.
I want to shout and celebrate immediately.
Everything feels extraordinary and thrilling.
My emotions feel elevated and unstoppable.
I feel euphoric and highly stimulated.

emotions.name: Calmness
texts: My breathing is slow and steady.
My thoughts feel clear and unhurried.
I feel balanced and mentally grounded.
There is no urgency in my body.
My muscles feel relaxed and loose.
I feel emotionally neutral and stable.
Silence feels comfortable rather than empty.
Iâ€™m present and at ease in this moment.
Nothing feels threatening or demanding.
I feel peacefully composed.

emotions.name: Pride
texts: I feel confident about what I have achieved.
A sense of accomplishment fills my chest.
I stand taller thinking about my success.
I feel validated and respected.
My efforts feel recognized and worthwhile.
I feel strong belief in my own abilities.
I feel dignified and self-assured.
There is satisfaction in knowing I did well.
I feel earned confidence rather than excitement.
My self-worth feels reinforced.

emotions.name: Hope
texts: I believe things can improve from here.
I feel a quiet optimism about the future.
Possibilities feel open rather than closed.
I sense forward movement despite uncertainty.
I feel encouraged to keep going.
The future feels lighter than the present.
I can imagine positive outcomes ahead.
My thoughts lean toward improvement and growth.
I feel patient but expectant.
There is gentle confidence in what lies ahead.

emotions.name: Disgust
texts: I feel a strong sense of revulsion.
My stomach turns unpleasantly.
I want to pull away instinctively.
This feels deeply unpleasant and wrong.
I feel contaminated by the situation.
My body reacts with rejection.
I feel intense aversion toward this.
Nausea rises quickly.
I feel compelled to avoid contact.
Everything about this feels repelling.

emotions.name: Resignation
texts: I feel drained of motivation.
I stop expecting things to change.
My resistance slowly fades away.
I feel emotionally exhausted.
There is no urge to fight anymore.
I accept the situation without energy.
Hope feels distant and unreachable.
My thoughts feel flat and surrendered.
I feel passive and disengaged.
I no longer feel invested in the outcome.
